{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/blog/vue-date-input-tag","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 400px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 100%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"vue-logo\"\n        title=\"vue-logo\"\n        src=\"/static/cf23526f451784ff137f161b8fe18d5a/e17e5/vue-logo.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/cf23526f451784ff137f161b8fe18d5a/8a4e8/vue-logo.png 150w,\n/static/cf23526f451784ff137f161b8fe18d5a/5a46d/vue-logo.png 300w,\n/static/cf23526f451784ff137f161b8fe18d5a/e17e5/vue-logo.png 400w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<div style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; color: grey; margin-bottom: 20px;\">this picture is from <a href=\"https://vuejs.org/\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" >here</a>\n</div>\n<p>In this article, I introduce you how to use a date input tag in the proper way with Vue.js.\nThe sample code of this article is <a href=\"https://github.com/Shunpoco/vue-ts-input-values-demo\">here</a>.</p>\n<h3>Problem</h3>\n<p>When I made a Vue component that contains a date input tag, I found that a value from the input tag returned its value as a string type. Even though I used TypeScript, it couldn't detect this behavior. I thought that it might cause bugs in the future (fig.1).</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&#x3C;div>\n    &#x3C;input type=\"data\" v-model=\"date1\" />\n    &#x3C;p>Time: {{ date1 }}&#x3C;/p>\n    &#x3C;p>A type of the value is: {{ function () { return typeof date1; }() }}&#x3C;/p>\n&#x3C;/div>\n...\nprivate date1!: Date;\n</code></pre>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.333333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"example1\"\n        title=\"example1\"\n        src=\"/static/141cfbf33e56d2075c1eae0afa350e3b/0a47e/example1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/141cfbf33e56d2075c1eae0afa350e3b/8a4e8/example1.png 150w,\n/static/141cfbf33e56d2075c1eae0afa350e3b/5a46d/example1.png 300w,\n/static/141cfbf33e56d2075c1eae0afa350e3b/0a47e/example1.png 600w,\n/static/141cfbf33e56d2075c1eae0afa350e3b/38af3/example1.png 894w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<div style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; color: grey; margin-bottom: 20px;\">Fig.1: Time becames just a date and a type of the value is string.</div>\n<h3>Solution</h3>\n<p>Instead of <code>v-model</code> directive, we use both <code>v-bind</code> and <code>v-on</code> directives. <code>v-model</code> is a syntax sugar of these two directives (see <a href=\"https://vuejs.org/v2/guide/forms.html\">the oficial docs</a>), we can replace <code>v-model</code> like this:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&#x3C;input type=\"date\"\n  v-bind:value=\"dateToStr(date2)\"\n  v-on:input=\"date2 = strToDate($event.target.value)\"\n/>\n\n...\n\n  private date2!: Date;\n\n  strToDate(str: string): Date {\n    return new Date(str);\n\n  dateToStr(date: Date): string {\n    const year = date.getFullYear();\n    const month = date.getMonth() + 1 &#x3C; 9 ? `0${date.getMonth() + 1}` : `${date.getMonth() + 1}`;\n    const day = date.getDate() &#x3C; 9 ? `0${date.getDate()}` : `${date.getDate()}`;\n    const strDate = `${year}-${month}-${day}`;\n    return strDate;\n  }\n</code></pre>\n<p>Then we define functions that converts a value from string type to Date Object type and vice versa, then call the functions in values of <code>v-bind</code> and <code>v-on:input</code>. Finally, the tag can pass the value in the proper type (fig.2).</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 600px; \"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 35.333333333333336%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"example2\"\n        title=\"example2\"\n        src=\"/static/7a3b934ea5888e10272e582d06858c27/0a47e/example2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7a3b934ea5888e10272e582d06858c27/8a4e8/example2.png 150w,\n/static/7a3b934ea5888e10272e582d06858c27/5a46d/example2.png 300w,\n/static/7a3b934ea5888e10272e582d06858c27/0a47e/example2.png 600w,\n/static/7a3b934ea5888e10272e582d06858c27/6c745/example2.png 893w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<div style=\"text-align: center; font-size: 14px; color: grey; margin-bottom: 20px;\">Fig.2: A type of the value is object and time shows datetime.</div>\n<h3>Conclusion</h3>\n<p>In order to use a date input tag with a proper type of value, we had better use both <code>v-bind</code> and <code>v-on:input</code> instead of using <code>v-model</code>.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"December 20, 2020","slug":"/blog/vue-date-input-tag","title":"How do we use a date input tag with Vue.js?","image":"vue-date-input/vue-logo.png"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/vue-date-input-tag"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864","63159454"]}